      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Therefore, it is imperative that local institutions be created to provide utilities to informal settlements.³ Wherever possible, they need to be provided first, so that it is not necessary to tear out existing homes or streets, which can be disruptive and expensive. In addition, the utilities can be brought to points along the streets where homes may be built, so that individual owners can connect to them safely. One way of doing this is by providing a prefabricated hookup unit, containing the basic provisions for kitchen and bath plumbing as well as electric and other services. A version of this, known as a “wet appliance,” is shown on the next page. It allows homeowners to build onto this module with their own construction over time.",
